data.title: Coinbase Q3 FY2025 earnings: Revenue $1.9B, EBITDA $801M. Crypto leading financial services shift. Derivatives grew 80% volume. USDC $15B held. Operating expenses $1.4B, net income $433M. Q4 outlook strong start. Expanding Everything Exchange. Base network token under exploration. Monetization via sequencer fees and ecosystem growth.
data.description: Coinbase Global, Inc. (NASDAQ: COIN) released its third-quarter financial results and held an earnings call where they discussed the company's performance. The total revenue reported for Q3 was $1.9 billion, with an adjusted EBITDA of $801 million. They ended Q3 with $11.9 billion in USD resources and $2.6 billion in long-term crypto investments. The company aims to increase economic freedom using crypto technology, with a focus on stablecoin adoption for global payments. In Q3, Coinbase customers held an average of $15 billion in USDC on the platform. The company saw strong growth in various areas, including spot coverage, derivatives products, and stablecoin adoption. They also announced plans for an Everything Exchange to trade every asset class. The Q4 outlook includes expectations of transaction revenue of $385 million and subscription revenue in the range of $710 to $790 million. The company plans to slow the rate of operating expense growth in Q4 compared to Q3 and is focused on building the Everything Exchange. Coinbase is exploring the idea of a Base Network token to bring more people onto the blockchain. The company monetizes through sequencer fees, indirect means, and plans to introduce new monetization opportunities in the future. Brian Armstrong, Co-Founder, and CEO highlighted the company's progress and future plans during the earnings call.
